%% Diagram: Undo with a concurrent operation interleaved (IP3 motivation)
%% Type: sequence
%%{init: {'htmlLabels': false}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    participant A as Site A
    participant S as Server
    participant B as Site B

    Note over A,B: Initial state: 'abc'
    A->>S: O1 = Ins(2, 'X')
    S->>S: Sequence O1 (rev 1) → 'abXc'
    S-->>B: Broadcast O1
    Note over A,B: Both sites: 'abXc'

    B->>S: O2 = Del(1) (concurrent edit by B on 'abXc')
    S->>S: Sequence O2 (rev 2) → 'aXc'
    S-->>A: Broadcast O2
    Note over A,B: Both sites: 'aXc'

    A->>S: Undo(O1) — A wants its insert reverted
    Note over S: Naive: invert O1 = Del(2). But position 2 in 'aXc' is 'c', not 'X'.
    S->>S: Apply IP3: transform inverse of O1 against O2 → Del(1)
    S->>S: Result: 'ac' (X removed, B's delete preserved)
    S-->>A: Ack undo
    S-->>B: Broadcast undo'
    Note over A,B: Both sites: 'ac'
